HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 502
By Hurt
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate Charlene Burpo on
her receipt of the Governor's Volunteer Stars
Award.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should specially
recognize those estimable citizens who have dedicated their time and energies to helping
others; and
WHEREAS, each year, 1.3 million Tennessee volunteers give over 99 million hours of
community service, contributing $2.6 billion to Tennessee's economy; and
WHEREAS, these volunteers are the backbone of our communities, and by donating
their time and talents to fulfill needs that would otherwise go unmet, they embody the spirit of
giving; and
WHEREAS, Charlene Burpo of Obion County is one such exemplary person, who is a
recipient of the Governor's Volunteer Stars Award in recognition of her laudable commitment to
her community; and
WHEREAS, throughout her many years of altruism, Ms. Burpo has worked with such
notable organizations as Main Street, the Carl Perkins Center, WestStar, Obion County Adult
Leadership, Run the Rails, the Kiwanis Club of Union City, and the Obion County Chamber of
Commerce to address the concrete needs of her fellow citizens, including economic growth,
quality of life, tourism, and leadership cultivation; and
WHEREAS, her apparent and impressive leadership qualities push her to the forefront of
every initiative she joins, and during her term as president of the Kiwanis Club of Union City,
she deployed the group's fervor and resources to install an inclusive playground in downtown
